    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#prefLabel> "Impriża Konġunta taċ-Ċipep"@mt, "Gemeinsames Unternehmen für Chips"@de, "Impresa comune «Chip»"@it, "Empresa Comum dos Circuitos Integrados"@pt, "Zajedničko poduzeće za čipove"@hr, "Entreprise commune «Semi-conducteurs»"@fr, "Skupno podjetje za čipe"@sl, "Společný podnik pro čipy"@cs, "Lustų bendroji įmonė"@lt, "Съвместно предприятие „Интегрални схеми“"@bg, "Csipekkel foglalkozó közös vállalkozás"@hu, "Chips Joint Undertaking"@en, "An Comhghnóthas um Shliseanna"@ga, "Kopuzņēmums “Mikroshēmas”"@lv, "Fællesforetagendet for mikrochips"@da, "Kiipide Ühisettevõte"@et, "Κοινή επιχείρηση «Μικροκυκλώματα»"@el, "Empresa Común para los Chips"@es, "Gemensamma företaget för halvledare"@sv, "Wspólne Przedsięwzięcie na rzecz Czipów"@pl, "Întreprinderea comună pentru cipuri"@ro, "Siruyhteisyritys"@fi, "Spoločný podnik pre čipy"@sk, "Gemeenschappelijke Onderneming “Chips”"@nl;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Chips JU is a public-private partnership that supports research, development, and manufacturing capacities in the European semiconductor ecosystem. It confronts semiconductor shortages and strengthens Europe’s digital autonomy. Chips JU serves as a powerhouse for innovation, uniting resources from various quarters. It draws strength from the European Union itself, tapping into the vast potential of programs like Horizon Europe and the Digital Europe Programme. Additionally, it collaborates with Member States and third countries associated with existing Union initiatives, and partners with the private sector. This pooling of resources creates a robust foundation for advancing semiconductor technologies."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "95221"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#ISBN_RG>, "10.2885"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#DOI_P>, "HS"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#OP_CAT>, "ECSEL"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#WHOISWHO>, "COB0001863"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>, "CJU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>, "CJU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "CJU"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#PUB_CORP>;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#altLabel> "ΚΕ «Μικροκυκλώματα»"@el, "Chips JU"@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#sameAs> <http://publications.europa.eu/resource/authority/corporate-body/CJU_2023_0>;
