    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "The European Union Aviation Safety Agency is the centrepiece of the European Union’s strategy for aviation safety. Its mission is to promote the highest common standards of safety and environmental protection in civil aviation. The Agency develops common safety and environmental rules at the European level. It monitors the implementation of standards through inspections in the Member States and provides the necessary technical expertise, training and research."@en;
    <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#notation> "TO"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#OP_CAT>, "9210"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#ISBN_RG>, "10.2822"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#DOI_P>, "EASA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#LAC>, "EASA"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#NAC>, "EASA_1"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#PUB_CORP>, "COB0001560"^^<http://publications.europa.eu/ontology/euvoc#XML_RECORD>;
